Privacy Policy for Das Electronic India Equipment Configuration App

Last Updated: 27-09-2023

Thank you for using the Das Electronic India Equipment Configuration App ("the App"). At Das Electronic India, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose your personal information when you use our App. Please take a moment to read this Privacy Policy carefully.

1. Information We Collect

1.1 Information You Provide to Us

When you use the App, you may voluntarily provide us with the following types of information:

- Personal Information: This includes information such as your name, email address, and contact details, which you may provide when contacting us for support or feedback.

- Configuration Data: The App may require you to input configuration settings for Das Electronic India equipment, such as Metal Detectors or Check Weighers. This data is used solely for the purpose of configuring the equipment and is not stored on our servers.

1.2 Automatically Collected Information

When you use the App, certain information may be automatically collected, including:

- Device Information: We may collect information about your mobile device, including its operating system, unique device identifiers, and other technical information.

- Usage Information: We collect information about how you use the App, such as the features you interact with and the actions you take.

2. How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

- To Provide and Maintain the App: We use your information to provide, maintain, and improve the App's functionality and performance.

- Customer Support: We may use your contact information to respond to your requests for customer support, technical assistance, or feedback.

- Analytics: We may use usage data to analyze the App's performance and make improvements based on user behavior and preferences.

3. Disclosure of Your Information

We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties except in the following circumstances:

- Service Providers: We may share your information with third-party service providers who assist us in operating the App and providing services to you. These service providers are contractually obligated to keep your information confidential and secure.

- Legal Compliance: We may disclose your information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, or legal processes.

4. Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Your Choices

You have the following choices regarding your personal information:

- Access and Correction: You can access, update, or correct your personal information by contacting us using the contact information provided below.

- Deletion: You can request the deletion of your personal information by contacting us, and we will make reasonable efforts to delete it unless retention is required by law or for legitimate business purposes.

6. Contact Us

If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or the use of your personal information, please contact us at:

info@daselectroni.com

7. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. The updated Privacy Policy will be posted on this page with a revised "Last Updated" date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.

By using the App, you signify your acceptance of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not use the App.

